The article discusses the proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump declaring October 9th as Leif Erikson Day. It highlights the significance of Leif Erikson's story and the values it represents in American culture. Leif Erikson, a Viking on a mission to Greenland, was blown off course and ended up discovering North America. The article also mentions the historical migration of Norwegian families to the United States, seeking religious freedom and safety. It acknowledges the contributions of Nordic Americans to American society, culture, and economy. Additionally, it emphasizes the strong diplomatic relationship between the United States and the Nordic countries, who are important economic partners and military allies. The proclamation calls upon Americans to celebrate Nordic American contributions with appropriate ceremonies and activities.